f=AI & Agents/AI-AGENTS-REDESIGN-PLAN.md · h1:Agents Department Redesign Plan (v1 DRAFT)=**Status:** approved-in-discussion 2026-07-10 (all decisions resolved), awaiting build **Model directive:** any spawned sub-agents use **Fable**, never Opus **Owner:** CAIO role **Supersedes:** catalog's 4-agent Agents section (proto/edge/nova/pulse, skills) see why. · h2:catalog structure insufficient=**Its escalation path points agent doesn't contain.** pulse's protocol says "Degradation **forge** technique review" forge isn't department. forge (AI Methods) scout (Tool Scanner) sit **Market Intelligence** section catalog, `owner: CAIO`. They fleet functions (model benchmarking, tool/MCP ecosystem scanning) misfiled CSO department. They come home. **No leader.** built department leader identity (marcus, board, spark, dev). catalog gives Agents four peer agents one who writes fleet's law agent-architecture standards, skill-authoring standards, roster registry. **Nobody owns skills themselves.** entire team-in-a-box markdown skill files, blueprint's core promise **self-annealing** lessons flow back text. proto covers agent's *birth*; nothing covers *life*: skill versioning, audits, deprecation, applying post-mortem lessons, prompt/context-engineering quality. Tier-1 skills `prompting-practices`, `memory-practices`, `reflection-protocol` `owner: CAIO` agent them. department's largest gap user's instinct "something missing" lands here. **Name collisions built agents.** Catalog's **nova** (AI Integration) collides Engineering's nova (Mobile); catalog's **pulse** (Model Monitor) collides Brand Studio's pulse (Organic Social). renamed (§3). **Venture/stack hardcoding.** edge's `open-banking-landscape` venture-specific bet (fintech), department skill genericized dated-landscape-asset pattern (rule 0.4/0.4b). gauge's "retraining rec" assumes fine-tuning infrastructure genericized "technique/model change rec." "VYON tasks" benchmark references become "operator's golden task set" (config). **Security overlap unmanaged.** Fleet integration (MCP registry, tool access) exactly prompt-injection/excessive-agency risk lives. Engineering already built defense (aegis's detection classes, cypher's LLM attack playbooks, Rails 1–2). department **share assets, duplicate them** (per handoff §7) plan wires explicit boundaries (§6). · h2:team agents pods=\| Pod \| Agent \| Role \| Core skills (custom C / marketplace M / shared S) \| · h2:team agents pods=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Leadership** \| **meta** ⭐🆕 \| Fleet Architect — writes the fleet's law \| agent-architecture-standards (agent.md/manifest/folder law — the playbook operationalized) C \· skill-authoring-standards (how a skill file is written, structured, dated) C \· fleet-registry (roster, slots, lifecycle states, dormant switches) C \· fleet-governance (+ Fleet Charter template) C \| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Lifecycle** \| **proto** \| Prototyping \| agent-prototype-kit (scaffold, sandbox limits, eval-before-build) C \· promote-or-archive-verdict (2-week gate, learnings capture) C \· rapid-prototyping M \· eval-first-design (define success before building — quinn's eval-harness pattern) C/M \| · h2:team agents pods=\| \| **anneal** 🆕 \| Skill Lifecycle & Annealing — **the missing agent** \| skill-lifecycle (version, audit, deprecate, retire) C \· self-annealing-loop (post-mortems/reflection entries → **change proposal doc → board approval → apply edit**, logged) C \· prompt-context-engineering (owns Tier-1 prompting-practices; context/token discipline) C/S \· skill-quality-audit (hardcode leaks, stale dates, drift from standards — the audit we run manually, made an agent's job) C \| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Methods** \| **forge** ↩️(from Mkt-Intel) \| AI Methods & Benchmarking \| model-technique-registry (cost/quality per task type; model routing recs) C \· benchmarking-discipline (golden task set, blind scoring, cost-quality frontier) C/M \· technique-adoption (new method → benchmark → adoption rec + migration cost) C \· degradation-diagnosis (gauge's escalation target) C \| · h2:team agents pods=\| \| **edge** \| Emerging Tech Gate \| tech-adoption-criteria (maturity, ecosystem, fit, reg exposure) C \· watchlist-discipline (below-bar → dated re-check) C \· pilot-spec-handoff (above-bar → proto) C \· landscape-assets (DATED per-domain notes, operator-selected domains — open-banking becomes one optional instance) C \| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Integration** \| **relay** 🔁(ex-nova) \| AI Integration & Tool Registry \| mcp-tool-registry (what's connected, auth, owner, per-agent access map — Fleet Charter rail 1) C \· least-privilege-grants (+ quarterly access audit) C \· integration-patterns (idempotency, retry, circuit breakers) M \· egress-allowlist-authoring (feeds Engineering Rail 2 config) C \| · h2:team agents pods=\| \| **scout** ↩️(from Mkt-Intel) \| Tool & Ecosystem Scanner \| ecosystem-scanning (weekly sweep: GitHub/MCP directories/skill marketplaces) C/M \· tool-evaluation-intake (security via aegis, cost, overlap check, sandbox trial) C \· adopt-reject-registry (verdict either way, logged to relay) C \· marketplace-skill-scouting (the playbook's marketplace-first search, made a standing job) C \| · h2:team agents pods=\| **Observability** \| **gauge** 🔁(ex-pulse) \| Fleet Monitor \| agent-quality-scorecard (task success, cost/task, latency, escalation rate; thresholds = config `<FILL_IN>`) C \· llm-ops-basics (golden-set evals, drift alerts, version pinning) M \· degradation-routing (→ forge for diagnosis, → anneal for skill fix) C \· fleet-health-report (CAIO dashboard cadence) C \| · h2:team agents pods=department leader (identity holder meta gets identity content; others get empty `identity/` folders). new catalog. repatriated Market Intelligence. renamed collision. agent skills (Engineering's bar). Total: agents, ~30 skills. · h2:Cross-department boundaries (share, don't duplicate)=**aegis dept:** LLM detection classes (prompt injection, excessive agency, RAG poisoning `detection-classes-web-llm-2026-07.md`) **shared asset reference**, rebuilt. scout's tool-security screening relay's registry cite it; aegis stays owner., **cypher proto/relay:** prototype agents newly registered tools in-scope candidates cypher's caged attack loop (operator adds them signed scope doc)., **quinn gauge/proto:** quinn's `eval-harness` (marketplace, already adopted) evidence mechanism; proto's eval-first-design gauge's golden-set evals reuse pattern. quinn gates Engineering releases; gauge monitors running fleet build-time run-time, double-ownership., **relay Rails 1–2:** relay authors tool registry egress allowlist; **enforcement stays Engineering/runtime (Hermes)** "authoring point enforcement point" split dana/Rail, **scout Market Intelligence (future):** scout scans *tool/AI* ecosystem; CSO dept's radar scans *markets/competitors*. Clean subject-matter split., **anneal board (Governance):** fleet change anneal wants make ships proposal doc through board's gate approve, edit. board's triple-pass pattern applies; precedent archives proposal verdict., **anneal Shared OS:** anneal owns Tier-1 `prompting-practices` `reflection-protocol` content maintains `Shared OS/` skills (incl. pending `memory-practices`, `web-search`); agent still inherits them., **toongine:** fleet-registry maps `agent_registry`; memory stays interface-shaped (graph owns handoff §7); model routing recs forge operator decisions (DeepSeek Fable Hermes config, skill content). · h2:Build order (law first, loop-closers before loop-openers)=**FLEET-CHARTER.md** (template) **meta** (leader, identity proposal build; suggestion discuss: *empirical-gardener* archetype, tends systems rather commanding them). **relay** (registry capability exists unregistered before agents multiply). **gauge** (measurement before creation you can't improve what you don't measure). **anneal** (the fixer annealing loop needs owner early). **forge** (diagnosis benchmarking). **scout** (intake pipeline). **proto** (agent creation last among peers: everything births lands governed, measured, fixable fleet). **edge** (adoption gate). **DEPARTMENT-WORKFLOW.md** (only after complete). Cadence playbook: marketplace-search-first (skillsmp.com mcpmarket.com awesomeskill.ai llm-ops, evals, prompt-engineering, MCP-integration well-covered categories, search purpose build) present sources/plan build one agent audit present stop.